&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 3 - Health Care Assistant Covid19 Community Testing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are recruiting experienced healthcare assistants to join our Urgent Care Service as a Covid-19 community tester. This role will support our Covid-19 testing to ensure that we can provide the safest care for both our staff and patients within the community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be performing Covid-19 swab tests within the community and will be visiting patients’ homes, care homes as well as supporting our static Covid-19 testing sites. This role requires lots of travel across the borough, and so it is essential that you hold a full driving license valid in the UK. However, you do not need a vehicle as you will also have access to a one of our cars during your working hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We will provide you with the necessary Personal Protective Equipment to carry out the role safely and you will be working in a supportive team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;About the Job&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform initial assessments on patients in a courteous and helpful manner trying to allay fears and anxieties that the patient may have&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertake Covid-19 swab tests on patients with potential infectious diseases either in their own home, care homes or at our testing centres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All testing procedures must be followed, and details recorded correctly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Always ensure effective infection, prevention and control measures are always adhered to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a seven-day service working 5 days out of 7 – working hours 9am to 5pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AfC Salary ranging from &lt;strong&gt;£19,737 - £21,142&lt;/strong&gt; per annum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong &lt;strong&gt;emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – &lt;strong&gt;27 days for new starters&lt;/strong&gt;, plus bank holidays. Increasing to &lt;strong&gt;29 days after 5 years&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;33 days after 10 years&lt;/strong&gt; NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent &lt;strong&gt;learning and development opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a &lt;strong&gt;new car&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous &lt;strong&gt;maternity, paternity&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;adoption leave&lt;/strong&gt; for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced &lt;strong&gt;IT enablement&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing &lt;strong&gt;independent support and advice for staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The 4 “must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must have NVQ level 3 in Health and Social Care or equivalent experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hold a full Driving Licence valid in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt; in a &lt;strong&gt;customer-based&lt;/strong&gt; environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent &lt;strong&gt;communication&lt;/strong&gt; skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call: Gemma Thomas on 01635 273508 or email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;gemma.thomas@berkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
